headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 28 points, five rebounds and eight assists as the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Charlotte Hornets 124-100 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 28 as the Grizzlies beat Hornets 124-100; Memphis' Wells breaks wrist in hard fall

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 28 points, Evan Mobley had 21 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists and the Cleveland Cavaliers clinched the top seed in the Eastern Conference with a 135-113 win over the Chicago Bulls on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers claim the No. 1 seed in the Eastern Conference with a 135-113 win over the Bulls

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 24 points and had 10 rebounds, Tyrese Haliburton had 22 points and the Indiana Pacers won their fifth straight game, 104-98 over the Washington Wizards on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam has 24 points and 10 rebounds as Pacers win 5th straight, 104-98 over Wizards

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 33 points and 10 rebounds and the Orlando Magic beat the Atlanta Hawks 119-112 on Tuesday night, taking command of the four-team play-in tournament race in the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero has 33 points and 10 rebounds as Magic turn back Hawks 119-112

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Trendon Watford scored 22 points, Drew Timme had 16 points and nine rebounds off the bench and the Brooklyn Nets beat the New Orleans Pelicans 119-114 on Tuesday night to snap a five-game home losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trendon Watford scores 22 and the Nets beat the Pelicans 119-114 to snap a 5-game home skid

events.name: Boston Celtics at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis made a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 40 seconds left in overtime after Jayson Tatum's 3-pointer with 2.9 seconds remaining forced the extra period, and the Boston Celtics completed a season sweep of the New York Knicks with a 119-117...
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis and Tatum make big 3-pointers as Celtics beat Knicks 119-117 in overtime

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 23 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists for his third straight triple-double as the Milwaukee Bucks erased a 24-point, fourth-quarter deficit to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 110-103 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks rally from 24-point, 4th-quarter deficit to beat Timberwolves 110-103

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 42 points, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Los Angeles Lakers 136-120 on Tuesday night after Luka Doncic was ejected.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 42 as NBA-leading Thunder top Lakers 136-120 after Doncic ejection

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 25 points, Brandin Podziemski added 22 and the Golden State Warriors coasted past the Phoenix Suns 133-95 on Tuesday night to keep pace in a crowded Western Conference playoff race.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 25 as the Warriors cruise past the Suns 133-95 and keep pace in West playoff race

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Ivica Zubac had 24 points and 20 rebounds, Norman Powell scored 25 points and the Los Angeles Clippers surged into fourth place in the Western Conference with a 122-117 victory over the San Antonio Spurs on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ivica Zubac leads surging Clippers past Spurs 122-117 and into fourth place in the crowded West
